# WritingInColor Software License Agreement

This Software License Agreement (the "Agreement") is made between the developers ("Developers"), WritingInColor ("Organization"), and New England Info Tech ("Contractor"), collectively referred to as the "Parties."

## 1. Grant of License
The Developers grant WritingInColor and the Contractor a non-exclusive, non-transferable, and non-sublicensable license to use, modify, and distribute the WritingInColor code ("Software") solely for the purposes of developing, maintaining, and operating the WritingInColor application.

## 2. Usage Rights
- WritingInColor and the Contractor may provide access to the Software to their respective employees, contractors, and agents as necessary to carry out the permitted uses.
- WritingInColor and the Contractor are prohibited from distributing, selling, licensing, or otherwise transferring the Software or any derivative works thereof to any third party without the express written consent of the Developers.

## 3. Developer Rights
- The Developers retain all rights, title, and interest in and to the Software, including all intellectual property rights.
- The Developers reserve the right to use any part of the Software, including code, algorithms, and methodologies, in any future projects, whether commercial or non-commercial.

## 4. Confidentiality
- WritingInColor and the Contractor agree to maintain the confidentiality of the Software and not disclose any part of it to any third party without the express written consent of the Developers.

## 5. Ownership
- The Developers retain ownership of the Software. This Agreement does not grant WritingInColor or the Contractor any ownership rights to the Software.

## 6. Term and Termination
- This Agreement is effective upon the date of execution and shall remain in effect until terminated by any of the Parties.
- WritingInColor and the Contractor may terminate this Agreement at any time by ceasing all use of the Software and destroying all copies of the Software.
- The Developers may terminate this Agreement if WritingInColor or the Contractor breaches any of its terms.

## 7. Limitation of Liability
- The Software is provided "as is" without any warranties of any kind. The Developers shall not be liable for any damages arising out of or in connection with the use of the Software.

## 8. Governing Law
- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [Your Jurisdiction].

## 9. Entire Agreement
- This Agreement constitutes the entire understanding between the Parties with respect to the subject matter and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, and negotiations.

By using the Software, WritingInColor and the Contractor acknowledge that they have read, understood, and agree to be bound by the terms of this Agreement.

